\ls5\ilvl1{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\'93de Man's argument is that departments of literature have denied their institutional identity as departments; they have constructed an institutional self-image which devalues their own purely institutional functions. Against such institutionalized anti-institutionalism de Man proposes a thorough reinvestment in the form of the department, as the basic structural unit of the university.\'94 which means no longer being 'large organizations in the service of everything except their own subject matter' but instead \'91much smaller units, dedicated to.. professional specialization\'92 (247)\
